WEBVTT

00:02.502 --> 00:04.137
[***]

00:04.170 --> 00:05.805
CHRIS ROCK:
<i>As rough as I had it as a kid,</i>

00:05.839 --> 00:09.442
<i>even I got excited</i>
<i>when Christmas came around.</i>

00:09.476 --> 00:11.511
Chris, how do you
spell "cabbage"?

00:11.544 --> 00:13.446
C-A-B-B-A-G-E.

00:13.480 --> 00:17.183
Thanks. "Cabbage Patch."
DREW: Oh, Chris!

00:17.217 --> 00:19.652
Look at this cool BMX bike.
Oh, that's cool.

00:19.686 --> 00:22.155
Chris, what are you
putting on your list?

00:22.188 --> 00:25.125
I'm not writing a list.
That's for kids.

00:25.158 --> 00:27.127
<i>I wasn't writing a list</i>

00:27.160 --> 00:30.630
<i>because the only thing I wanted</i>
<i>was a portable cassette player.</i>

00:30.663 --> 00:33.800
<i>Having a Walkman meant you</i>
<i>could even listen to bad music</i>

00:33.833 --> 00:35.502
<i>and nobody had to know.</i>

00:35.535 --> 00:38.271
<i>I had been leaving that ad</i>
<i>all over the house,</i>

00:38.304 --> 00:41.274
<i>so I was pretty sure</i>
<i>my mother got the hint.</i>

00:41.307 --> 00:43.410
[***]

01:02.662 --> 01:05.598
<i>Since I only wanted one gift,</i>
<i>I knew I'd get it.</i>

01:05.632 --> 01:08.535
<i>This was going to be</i>
<i>the best Christmas ever.</i>

01:08.568 --> 01:09.469
[GROANS]

01:09.502 --> 01:11.771
Happy Kwanza, Kunta Kinte.

01:11.805 --> 01:13.873
<i>Well, maybe not</i>ever.

01:13.907 --> 01:16.376
[***]

01:21.948 --> 01:24.317
<i>* Aw, make it funky now </i>

01:48.742 --> 01:50.643
I'm getting a ColecoVision.
Wait.

01:50.677 --> 01:53.380
You have an Atari and
you're getting a ColecoVision?

01:53.413 --> 01:55.215
Yeah. What are you getting?

01:55.248 --> 01:56.850
I'm getting a Walkman.

01:56.883 --> 01:58.518
No way.

01:58.551 --> 02:00.687
It's the only thing
I've been asking for.

02:00.720 --> 02:03.256
I would kill for one
of those. You're so lucky.

02:03.289 --> 02:04.758
How come your dad
doesn't get you one?

02:04.791 --> 02:06.760
Censorship.
He wants to makes sure

02:06.793 --> 02:08.828
he can hear the music
I'm listening to.

02:08.862 --> 02:11.831
<i>First rap was fun,</i>
<i>then rap was gun.</i>

02:11.865 --> 02:14.801
Let me go, you bitches.
You're punks, both of you.

02:14.834 --> 02:18.538
West side! West side!
Jeez, kid, will you shut up?

02:18.571 --> 02:20.807
<i>Years later,</i>
<i>Greg played some Ice Cube</i>

02:20.840 --> 02:22.475
<i>and his own father shot him.</i>

02:22.509 --> 02:26.780
Class, since this
is the season of giving,

02:26.813 --> 02:29.783
I'd like you all to bring in
canned food items,

02:29.816 --> 02:33.520
so we can donate them
to those less fortunate.

02:33.553 --> 02:35.622
<i>It's funny how most people</i>
<i>only think about</i>

02:35.655 --> 02:37.590
<i>feeding the needy</i>
<i>during Christmas.</i>

02:37.624 --> 02:39.759
<i>I'm sure there's a lot</i>
<i>of hungry people</i>

02:39.793 --> 02:41.528
<i>during President's Day.</i>

02:41.561 --> 02:43.697
Yes, Chris?
Do we have to bring in cans?

02:43.730 --> 02:45.665
Can we bring in, like,
boxes of food?

02:45.699 --> 02:47.634
You don't have
to bring anything,

02:47.667 --> 02:50.503
but that's
very thoughtful of you.

02:50.537 --> 02:53.506
I know this time of year
must be hard for your family.

02:53.540 --> 02:56.409
No. We're doing fine.

02:56.443 --> 02:59.579
I know. I know.

02:59.612 --> 03:01.681
<i>She made it seem</i>
<i>like we were having</i>

03:01.715 --> 03:04.284
<i>a bowl of steam</i>
<i>for dinner that night.</i>

03:04.317 --> 03:05.452
[JULIUS YELPS]

03:05.485 --> 03:07.354
Who used up all the hot water?

03:07.387 --> 03:08.555
It's five degrees outside.

03:08.588 --> 03:10.423
What you trying to do,
kill me?

03:10.457 --> 03:12.625
Chris said it was cool
when he took a shower earlier.

03:12.659 --> 03:15.795
Oh! The hot water heater's
probably broken again.

03:15.829 --> 03:18.565
Think you can fix it?
I'm already holding it together

03:18.598 --> 03:20.300
with duct tape and hangers.

03:20.333 --> 03:21.835
We're just gonna have
to replace it.

03:21.868 --> 03:24.738
Well, baby, how much
do you think that's gonna cost?

03:24.771 --> 03:26.473
More than I got.

03:26.506 --> 03:28.842
Will we have enough money
to buy Christmas presents?

03:28.875 --> 03:31.678
I thought you finished shopping.
I bought a few things,

03:31.711 --> 03:34.347
but I have got to get
that Walkman for Chris.

03:34.381 --> 03:36.583
He's been giving me hints
since Thanksgiving.

03:36.616 --> 03:39.319
These kids get
too many gifts on Christmas.

03:39.352 --> 03:41.454
When I was a kid,
instead of buying gifts,

03:41.488 --> 03:43.590
my father used to call
the cops on Christmas

03:43.623 --> 03:45.425
and tell us
the house got robbed.

03:45.458 --> 03:47.594
<i>In order to make</i>
<i>extra money for Christmas,</i>

03:47.627 --> 03:49.062
<i>my father would do any job.</i>

03:49.095 --> 03:50.730
That'll be $30.

03:50.764 --> 03:53.400
<i>He worked as a cab driver.</i>
That's okay.

03:53.433 --> 03:55.335
<i>It was easy for him</i>
<i>to pick up odd jobs</i>

03:55.368 --> 03:57.037
<i>for extra money</i>
<i>when he needed it.</i>

03:57.070 --> 03:58.571
Merry Christmas.

03:58.605 --> 03:59.706
Lint roll, sir?
Yeah.

03:59.739 --> 04:01.841
<i>He worked as a lint roller.</i>

04:03.677 --> 04:05.612
Thank you.

04:05.645 --> 04:09.015
<i>He even worked</i>
<i>as an oil taster.</i>

04:09.049 --> 04:12.352
This is 10-W 30.
You need 10-W 40.

04:12.385 --> 04:14.521
<i>Now, that's a father.</i>

04:16.122 --> 04:18.324
TONYA:
Drew.

04:18.358 --> 04:19.592
Drew.

04:21.795 --> 04:22.829
Drew!
Ow!

04:22.862 --> 04:25.932
What'd you do that for?
How do you spell "Malibu"?

04:25.965 --> 04:29.903
M-A-L-I-BOO?

04:29.936 --> 04:32.505
You still writing that
stupid Christmas list?

04:32.539 --> 04:34.507
It's not stupid.
Yes, it is.

04:34.541 --> 04:36.843
Everybody knows there's
no Santa Claus, Tonya.

04:36.876 --> 04:38.078
That's not true.

04:38.111 --> 04:40.547
And it's not stupid.
You're stupid.

04:40.580 --> 04:42.582
You're stupid.
You're stupid.

04:42.615 --> 04:44.651
ROCHELLE:
Drew, stop calling
your sister stupid!

04:44.684 --> 04:46.519
<i>My mother had amazing hearing.</i>

04:46.553 --> 04:50.523
<i>We couldn't do anything in our</i>
<i>house without her hearing it.</i>

04:51.925 --> 04:55.729
Chris! Quit throwing cotton
balls all over the place!

04:57.697 --> 05:00.533
What are y'all arguing about?
Nothing.

05:00.567 --> 05:04.571
Drew said there's
no such thing as Santa Claus.

05:04.604 --> 05:06.673
What are you talking about, boy?

05:06.706 --> 05:09.642
Of course there's
a Santa Claus, baby.

05:09.676 --> 05:11.478
CHRIS: Hey.
DREW: What's up, bro?

05:11.511 --> 05:13.079
We're having
a food drive at school.

05:13.113 --> 05:15.715
Can I bring some canned goods?
Okay.

05:15.749 --> 05:18.651
But don't take generic brands.
Only store brands.

05:18.685 --> 05:20.520
I do not want
those people thinking

05:20.553 --> 05:22.022
we can't afford to donate food.

05:22.055 --> 05:24.157
<i>My mother would give away</i>
<i>all the food we had</i>

05:24.190 --> 05:27.827
<i>if she thought it would prove</i>
<i>we didn't need it.</i>

05:27.861 --> 05:29.596
How come you said
my list is stupid?

05:29.629 --> 05:32.632
Because everybody knows
there's no Santa Claus.

05:32.665 --> 05:35.135
Come here, let me
show you something.

05:36.903 --> 05:38.505
Where are we going?

05:38.538 --> 05:39.973
I'm taking you to the toys.

05:40.006 --> 05:41.808
Santa doesn't come
down the chimney.

05:41.841 --> 05:44.044
We don't even have
a chimney, we have radiators.

05:44.077 --> 05:46.913
You ever heard of Santa Claus
coming through radiators?

05:46.946 --> 05:48.982
But how can we have
our toys already

05:49.015 --> 05:52.018
if I haven't even
finished my list?

05:52.052 --> 05:54.020
Because.

05:54.054 --> 05:56.489
Hey, man. What you doing?

05:56.523 --> 05:59.693
I'm taking canned goods
to school for the needy.

05:59.726 --> 06:04.798
[CASH REGISTER CLICKING, DINGS]

06:04.831 --> 06:07.033
Man, that's $2.89 cent
worth of food.

06:07.067 --> 06:10.003
What you trying to do,
feed the needy or be the needy?

06:10.036 --> 06:11.838
Rochelle!
Julius!

06:11.871 --> 06:13.740
[***]

06:15.742 --> 06:18.478
<i>My parents tried not argue</i>
<i>in front of the kids,</i>

06:18.511 --> 06:21.181
<i>so instead,</i>
<i>they just made faces.</i>

06:26.786 --> 06:29.989
<i>They make curse-out faces too,</i>
<i>but we can't show you those.</i>

06:30.023 --> 06:33.026
<i>Meanwhile, Drew was showing</i>
<i>Tanya something</i>

06:33.059 --> 06:35.895
<i>no kid should see.</i>

06:35.929 --> 06:37.997
See, I told you.

06:39.065 --> 06:41.001
[***]

06:44.537 --> 06:45.538
[DOOR SLAMS]

06:45.572 --> 06:46.806
Whoa! Cool!

06:51.711 --> 06:54.014
<i>Tonya wasn't the only one</i>
<i>having a bad day.</i>

06:54.047 --> 06:55.882
Is there something wrong?

06:57.584 --> 06:58.985
Have a seat, baby.

06:59.019 --> 07:00.920
<i>The last time they asked me</i>
<i>to sit down</i>

07:00.954 --> 07:03.957
<i>before they told me something,</i>
<i>The Jackson Five broke up.</i>

07:03.990 --> 07:05.792
Hey, Chris. Heh.

07:05.825 --> 07:08.094
Um, baby, look, I know you've
been looking forward

07:08.128 --> 07:10.663
to getting that new Walkman
for Christmas.

07:10.697 --> 07:12.665
And, Chris, I've always
wanted my kids

07:12.699 --> 07:15.502
to have a better Christmas
than I had growing up.

07:15.535 --> 07:18.538
But the older you get,
the more you learn

07:18.571 --> 07:20.240
about the sacrifices
you have to make.

07:20.273 --> 07:23.043
Sacrifices?

07:23.076 --> 07:25.111
Uh...

07:25.145 --> 07:26.646
Uh...

07:26.680 --> 07:28.682
Like not getting
a new pair of work boots

07:28.715 --> 07:29.816
so you kids can have shoes.

07:29.849 --> 07:31.685
Or like taking
the subway to work

07:31.718 --> 07:33.653
so your wife can use the car.

07:39.726 --> 07:42.529
Mom, Dad, I'm 13.

07:42.562 --> 07:44.597
You're not getting
a present for Christmas.

07:44.631 --> 07:47.767
<i>He said that</i>
<i>like we're out of bacon.</i>

07:47.801 --> 07:49.703
We gotta buy
a new water heater.

07:49.736 --> 07:51.571
Well, then, we need a plan

07:51.604 --> 07:53.640
to tell Drew and Tonya.
Tell them what?

07:53.673 --> 07:54.974
That they're not
getting presents.

07:55.008 --> 07:57.043
Who said they weren't getting
anything?

07:58.611 --> 08:01.214
Wait, they're getting stuff
and I'm not?

08:01.247 --> 08:03.049
You're older, Chris.

08:03.083 --> 08:05.285
They wouldn't understand.

08:06.820 --> 08:08.555
Am I gonna get anything?

08:08.588 --> 08:13.860
Oh, baby, you'll be able to use
up all the hot water you want.

08:13.893 --> 08:16.129
<i>So all I'm getting</i>
<i>is a clean ass?</i>

08:16.162 --> 08:17.797
Steaming hot.

08:17.831 --> 08:21.301
<i>* Everybody hates Chris </i>

08:29.776 --> 08:32.078
So you're not getting
anything for Christmas?

08:32.112 --> 08:33.580
Nope.

08:33.613 --> 08:35.248
Man, nothing for Christmas?

08:35.281 --> 08:37.784
Isn't that considered
child abuse?

08:37.817 --> 08:39.586
Sure does feel like it.

08:39.619 --> 08:41.321
They'll put something
in your stocking.

08:41.354 --> 08:43.923
Maybe some leftover sausage.

08:43.957 --> 08:47.027
There's gotta be
a law against this.

08:47.060 --> 08:49.863
Oh, Chris, look at you.

08:49.896 --> 08:51.898
You didn't have
to bring any food.

08:51.931 --> 08:55.001
Sometimes I forget
how strong your people are.

08:55.035 --> 08:56.936
What do you mean,
how strong my people are?

08:56.970 --> 09:00.607
What do I mean,
how strong your people are?

09:00.640 --> 09:03.209
You shall overcome someday.

09:03.243 --> 09:07.147
See me after class.
I have something for you.

09:07.180 --> 09:08.648
Okay.

09:10.150 --> 09:12.752
<i>Do I look like</i>
<i>Malcolm X to you, lady?</i>

09:12.786 --> 09:15.321
<i>How would you like</i>
<i>to overcome a brick?</i>

09:21.361 --> 09:24.664
Tonya, I thought you were
gonna put up the decorations.

09:24.698 --> 09:26.833
I don't want to now.

09:26.866 --> 09:30.303
Why not?
Because.

09:30.337 --> 09:33.173
You and Daddy lied to me.

09:33.206 --> 09:35.041
We lied to you? About what?

09:35.075 --> 09:38.244
I know there's no such thing
as Santa Claus.

09:38.278 --> 09:41.114
<i>When my mother heard</i>
<i>Tonya say those words,</i>

09:41.147 --> 09:43.717
<i>it was like she wasn't</i>
<i>her baby anymore.</i>

09:43.750 --> 09:45.185
What else did you
lie to me about?

09:45.218 --> 09:47.053
Are you gonna kick me out
if I get pregnant?

09:47.087 --> 09:49.155
Is it true you ain't
taking care of no baby?

09:49.189 --> 09:50.890
Can I really not bring
a white boy home?

09:50.924 --> 09:52.225
Does the Foreman Grill
really knock out the fat?

09:52.258 --> 09:54.060
Can I really get a loan
with no money down?

09:54.094 --> 09:57.864
Are you my real mother?
Mama, I want answers.

09:57.897 --> 10:02.302
Tonya, like Mommy told you,
there<i>is</i>a Santa Claus.

10:02.335 --> 10:06.172
So how come there's a room
upstairs full of presents?

10:06.206 --> 10:08.808
Who told you that?
Drew showed me.

10:08.842 --> 10:12.078
Drew, get in here!

10:12.112 --> 10:13.013
Yes, Mom?

10:13.046 --> 10:16.349
Did you show Tonya
the presents upstairs?

10:16.383 --> 10:18.151
Yeah.

10:18.184 --> 10:21.021
We need to talk.

10:21.054 --> 10:22.222
Uh...no.

10:22.255 --> 10:24.157
Hold on, Mama. No, no.

10:24.190 --> 10:26.993
<i>My mother talked about beating</i>
<i>us all the time,</i>

10:27.027 --> 10:28.862
<i>but the only time</i>
<i>she ever beat us</i>

10:28.895 --> 10:30.764
<i>is when she said</i>
<i>she wanted to talk.</i>

10:30.797 --> 10:33.299
<i>And she talked the hell</i>
<i>out of Drew that night.</i>

10:33.333 --> 10:35.902
[DREW GROANING, SCREAMS]

10:37.370 --> 10:38.938
[GRUNTS]

10:41.107 --> 10:44.844
Oh.
Well, what's all this stuff?

10:44.878 --> 10:46.813
I got it from my teacher.
Hm.

10:46.846 --> 10:50.316
She thinks that we're
underprivileged and starving.

10:50.350 --> 10:53.119
Oh, no. Mm-mm.

10:53.153 --> 10:54.721
Absolutely not.

10:54.754 --> 10:56.890
I am not gonna have
them people thinking

10:56.923 --> 10:58.858
that we don't have
anything to eat.

10:58.892 --> 11:00.960
<i>She wasn't too proud</i>
<i>to take those olives.</i>

11:00.994 --> 11:02.796
Where you going?
I'm taking this

11:02.829 --> 11:03.930
to put more food in it.

11:03.963 --> 11:05.265
You're taking this back.

11:05.298 --> 11:06.966
<i>My mother was so upset</i>

11:07.000 --> 11:08.935
<i>about people thinking</i>
<i>we needed charity,</i>

11:08.968 --> 11:10.837
<i>she almost forgot</i>
<i>she felt guilty</i>

11:10.870 --> 11:12.272
<i>about not getting me a gift.</i>

11:12.305 --> 11:13.373
Chris, wait a minute.

11:13.406 --> 11:16.109
Look, I'm sorry.

11:16.142 --> 11:18.244
I know all of this
is not your fault.

11:18.278 --> 11:21.214
I know it seems kind of crazy
with me giving back free food

11:21.247 --> 11:24.150
when we can't even afford
to buy you a Christmas gift.

11:24.184 --> 11:26.252
It's okay.

11:26.286 --> 11:29.489
<i>After that, my mother gave me</i>
<i>the one gift she could afford.</i>

11:29.522 --> 11:32.425
<i>She was really nice to me!</i>

11:32.459 --> 11:36.229
<i>Who needs Christmas when all</i>
<i>your wildest dreams come true?</i>

11:36.262 --> 11:38.264
Chris gets the big piece.

11:40.800 --> 11:42.802
<i>I got the big piece of chicken.</i>

11:42.836 --> 11:44.771
[***]

11:48.108 --> 11:49.109
Merry Christmas.

11:53.480 --> 11:55.448
<i>I didn't have to do any chores.</i>

11:55.482 --> 11:56.950
Tonya, wash the dishes.

11:56.983 --> 11:58.785
I thought Chris
had to do 'em.

11:58.818 --> 12:01.521
You thought wrong.

12:01.554 --> 12:03.323
<i>I got Tonya in trouble.</i>

12:03.356 --> 12:05.025
Ow! Ow!

12:05.058 --> 12:07.961
Mama, Tonya hit me twice.

12:09.329 --> 12:12.065
<i>It felt so good, I was thinking</i>
<i>what life would be like</i>

12:12.098 --> 12:13.533
<i>if I never got a present.</i>

12:13.566 --> 12:15.402
Get up and let your brother
watch TV.

12:15.435 --> 12:17.904
But, Ma!
But nothing! Get up.

12:20.073 --> 12:23.243
<i>I wondered what I could get</i>
<i>if the roof caved in.</i>

12:26.246 --> 12:27.313
Mwah!

12:29.983 --> 12:32.318
Hey, Drew, can you
pass me the remote?

12:32.352 --> 12:34.387
Tsk, yeah, right.

12:34.421 --> 12:36.122
Ma...

12:36.156 --> 12:37.424
[GROANS]

12:37.457 --> 12:39.159
[MUTTERING]

12:42.095 --> 12:44.064
<i>I couldn't believe</i>
<i>how good I had it.</i>

12:44.097 --> 12:46.232
<i>Meanwhile,</i>
<i>Tonya didn't believe anything.</i>

12:46.266 --> 12:49.869
Mama, is cornbread
made of corn?

12:49.903 --> 12:51.304
Mm, no.

12:51.338 --> 12:54.874
I think it's made
of cornmeal. Why?

12:54.908 --> 12:57.043
Just checking.
DREW: Why, you want Santa Claus

12:57.077 --> 12:58.978
to bring you
some cornbread for Christmas?

12:59.012 --> 13:00.513
He could bring it with
your Cabbage Patch Doll.

13:00.547 --> 13:05.051
Hey, hey. Stop it. Okay? Enough.
JULIUS: Leave your sister alone.

13:05.085 --> 13:07.854
Drew, you believed in the Easter
Bunny till about her age.

13:07.887 --> 13:09.622
Chris, you near lost
all your teeth

13:09.656 --> 13:12.892
before you stopped believing
in the Tooth Fairy.

13:14.294 --> 13:17.530
There's no Easter Bunny
or Tooth Fairy, either?

13:17.564 --> 13:19.399
Uh...
No, baby, he...

13:19.432 --> 13:20.900
He didn't mean that.

13:20.934 --> 13:23.636
Somebody better give me
my teeth back.

13:23.670 --> 13:26.206
Baby, I didn't mean it!
I didn't mean it!

13:26.239 --> 13:29.542
Julius! I can't believe you!
I want my teeth back!

13:29.576 --> 13:31.144
Baby, no...
Tonya!

13:31.177 --> 13:32.545
We were joking!
It's a joke!

13:32.579 --> 13:36.016
It's a... Ha-ha! It's a joke!

13:38.318 --> 13:40.987
That's her. She said Santa
can't come to our house,

13:41.021 --> 13:42.889
'cause all we have
is space heaters.

13:42.922 --> 13:44.657
Santa can't come
through a space heater.

13:44.691 --> 13:46.559
What kind of children
are you raising?

13:46.593 --> 13:48.361
This girl's going around
crushing dreams.

13:48.395 --> 13:50.964
Is that what you want her to be?
A dream crusher?

13:50.997 --> 13:53.333
No, but I--
That girl needs to be stopped.

13:55.135 --> 13:58.138
Tonya!
It's the truth!

13:58.171 --> 14:01.341
<i>Normally, my mother would smack</i>
<i>the grease out of Tonya's hair.</i>

14:01.374 --> 14:04.044
<i>But she couldn't smack her</i>
<i>for telling the truth.</i>

14:04.077 --> 14:05.578
GREG:
What's that?

14:05.612 --> 14:07.480
My mom made me bring
all this stuff back

14:07.514 --> 14:10.583
to prove that we can afford
to donate food.

14:10.617 --> 14:13.586
Hey, yo, I got
something for you.

14:13.620 --> 14:16.156
Thanks! What's this?
Open it.

14:18.358 --> 14:20.994
<i>"Computer Games."</i>
Who is it?

14:21.027 --> 14:22.228
George Clinton.

14:22.262 --> 14:24.164
There's a song on there,
"Atomic Dog,"

14:24.197 --> 14:26.199
I heard it on the radio.
It's really funny.

14:26.232 --> 14:28.034
Think I'll like it?
I don't know.

14:28.068 --> 14:30.470
When you finally get your
Walkman, you'll have a tape.

14:30.503 --> 14:33.206
<i>I always liked</i>
<i>that Greg was so optimistic.</i>

14:33.239 --> 14:34.941
<i>To this day, he still thinks</i>

14:34.974 --> 14:37.010
<i>Al B. Sure's gonna make</i>
<i>a comeback.</i>

14:37.043 --> 14:38.645
[BELL RINGS]

14:40.647 --> 14:45.385
But if Santa Claus is not real,
why do people make it up?

14:45.418 --> 14:48.455
Tonya, Santa is
just a way to teach kids

14:48.488 --> 14:50.323
about the spirit of giving.

14:50.357 --> 14:53.293
He's just a symbol,
that's all.

14:53.326 --> 14:54.394
Oh.

14:55.662 --> 14:57.997
Tonya, you're a big girl,

14:58.031 --> 15:00.700
and now that you're old
enough to know the truth,

15:00.734 --> 15:02.202
it's your responsibility

15:02.235 --> 15:04.371
to not spoil it
for other kids, okay?

15:04.404 --> 15:07.374
Because you want to give them
something to believe in.

15:07.407 --> 15:09.442
Exactly.

15:09.476 --> 15:12.045
That's my big girl. Mwah!

15:12.078 --> 15:14.080
So you do understand.

15:14.114 --> 15:17.650
Yeah. It's okay to lie.

15:17.684 --> 15:20.120
Aw, good night, Mommy.

15:20.153 --> 15:22.422
<i>You think explaining</i>
<i>Santa Claus to Tonya was hard,</i>

15:22.455 --> 15:25.392
<i>you should have been there</i>
<i>for the birds and the bees.</i>

15:25.425 --> 15:28.028
Ew, that's nasty!

15:28.061 --> 15:30.163
[***]

15:32.599 --> 15:37.137
<i>Nobody ever seems to get</i>
<i>any sleep on Christmas Eve.</i>

15:39.039 --> 15:42.042
<i>Everybody's up</i>
<i>for different reasons.</i>

15:42.075 --> 15:43.309
What you doing, baby?

15:43.343 --> 15:45.545
Setting out
milk and cookies.

15:45.578 --> 15:47.147
We talked about this.

15:47.180 --> 15:50.116
We did.
And they're not for Santa.

15:50.150 --> 15:51.618
They're for you.

15:51.651 --> 15:53.153
[CHUCKLES]

15:53.186 --> 15:55.455
Thank you, baby.

15:59.059 --> 16:00.727
<i>But since I wasn't getting</i>
<i>anything,</i>

16:00.760 --> 16:03.029
<i>I didn't have that problem.</i>

16:03.063 --> 16:04.731
[SNORING]

16:07.434 --> 16:11.438
<i>On Christmas morning, I even</i>
<i>took my time going downstairs.</i>

16:18.511 --> 16:20.714
<i>Now that Tonya knew there</i>
<i>wasn't a Santa Claus,</i>

16:20.747 --> 16:23.249
<i>her complaints went</i>
<i>directly to my mother.</i>

16:23.283 --> 16:26.753
Mama, I wanted a Cabbage Patch
Doll with long hair.

16:26.786 --> 16:29.322
How about you have
no doll with no hair?

16:29.356 --> 16:32.759
Oh, thank you.
Okay.

16:32.792 --> 16:35.128
Chris, this one
is for you, baby.

16:35.161 --> 16:37.430
Is it a new album?
Open it and find out.

16:37.464 --> 16:40.066
They were giving those away
at the doctor's office

16:40.100 --> 16:41.334
I deliver papers to.

16:41.368 --> 16:43.069
Thought you could use it
for school.

16:43.103 --> 16:45.138
Thanks. I will.

16:45.171 --> 16:48.108
Hey, Chris, what'd you get?

16:48.141 --> 16:49.743
A calendar.

16:49.776 --> 16:51.344
A calendar?

16:51.378 --> 16:53.847
Yeah, that's what I wanted.

16:53.880 --> 16:56.149
See, now, look here.
Did you know that May

16:56.182 --> 16:58.184
is High Blood Pressure Month?
DREW & TONYA: No.

16:58.218 --> 17:00.387
You would if you had a calendar.
ROCHELLE: See?

17:00.420 --> 17:02.689
All y'all should ask
for calendars next year.

17:02.722 --> 17:05.492
JULIUS: That's a good idea.
Hey, Chris, wanna go

17:05.525 --> 17:09.362
ride my bike outside later?
<i>By "later," he meant summer.</i>

17:09.396 --> 17:13.466
Yeah, sure.
Hey, Chris. You can have this.

17:15.135 --> 17:17.671
Are you sure?
Yeah. I'm sure.

17:17.704 --> 17:19.839
Baby, that's so nice.

17:19.873 --> 17:23.243
<i>That's what I thought too.</i>

17:23.276 --> 17:24.811
Yes! I win again!

17:24.844 --> 17:27.447
In your face! Ooh!

17:29.516 --> 17:31.551
<i>What now?</i>
<i>I don't get New Year's?</i>

17:31.584 --> 17:33.286
Mwah! Thank you.

17:33.319 --> 17:35.188
For what?
For the way you've handled

17:35.221 --> 17:36.389
not getting what you wanted.

17:36.423 --> 17:39.125
You've really made
us proud, man.

17:39.159 --> 17:40.460
Drew and Tonya are kids.

17:40.493 --> 17:42.395
They need Christmas presents
more than me.

17:42.429 --> 17:44.431
You know, you're really
growing up, Chris.

17:44.464 --> 17:47.334
It's kind of nice having
another man around the house.

17:47.367 --> 17:49.602
<i>It was weird.</i>
<i>That morning with my parents</i>

17:49.636 --> 17:53.173
<i>felt better</i>
<i>than any gift I ever got.</i>

17:53.206 --> 17:55.608
Here you go.
What's this?

17:55.642 --> 17:58.311
Toy store coupon,
50 percent off.

17:58.345 --> 18:00.647
It's good till March.

18:00.680 --> 18:03.450
<i>By the end of the day,</i>
<i>it didn't even matter anymore</i>

18:03.483 --> 18:06.886
<i>that I didn't have a gift,</i>
<i>because I had a good day.</i>

18:06.920 --> 18:09.589
<i>And right now, I'm with</i>
<i>Mrs. Vivian Morello.</i>

18:09.622 --> 18:10.824
Hey, that's my teacher.

18:10.857 --> 18:12.392
It is?
Mm-hm.

18:12.425 --> 18:14.694
<i>Every year,</i>
<i>my students collect food</i>

18:14.728 --> 18:18.264
<i>for the very poorest,</i>
<i>most destitute</i>

18:18.298 --> 18:20.166
<i>and neediest families.</i>

18:20.200 --> 18:21.468
<i>These people are so poor,</i>

18:21.501 --> 18:23.169
<i>they probably don't</i>
<i>have anything</i>

18:23.203 --> 18:24.704
<i>but the clothes on their backs.</i>

18:24.738 --> 18:27.474
<i>Even though they're</i>
<i>embarrassingly underprivileged,</i>

18:27.507 --> 18:31.211
<i>they're just too proud</i>
<i>to ask for help.</i>

18:31.244 --> 18:34.614
<i>Too proud to ask for help.</i>
<i>And they're poor.</i>

18:34.647 --> 18:38.251
<i>Tonight, we're going to give</i>
<i>a family this basket.</i>

18:38.284 --> 18:41.321
Now, who wants somebody
coming to their door on TV

18:41.354 --> 18:44.257
talking about
how poor they are?

18:44.290 --> 18:47.193
<i>This is so exciting.</i>

18:47.227 --> 18:48.595
[DOORBELL BUZZES]
[KNOCKING]

18:48.628 --> 18:50.196
Mm, I'll get it.

18:51.297 --> 18:52.632
<i>You got it?</i>

18:56.269 --> 18:57.704
BOTH:
Merry Christmas!

18:58.772 --> 19:01.441
Chris!

19:01.474 --> 19:05.645
<i>* Everybody hates Chris </i>

19:10.583 --> 19:13.653
CHRIS ROCK:
<i>Stay tuned for scenes</i>
<i>from our next episode.</i>

19:15.789 --> 19:19.292
[***]

19:19.325 --> 19:22.228
<i>* Aw, make it funky now </i>
